 Middle Ages and gave rise to surnames, are extinct.  See also  Rupert ."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705190,"age":20,"year":"1290","julianDay":2192224,"title":"Jews Expelled From England","description":"After years of anti-Semitic behavior, King Edward I expelled Jews from England in 1290.","jurisdictionLevel":0},{"id":1705191,"age":45,"year":"1315","toYear":"1317","julianDay":2201354,"title":"Famine Strikes Europe","description":"A famine caused by cold winters and wet summers across Europe caused millions to die due to starvation. Desperation from hunger caused high levels of crime, stampedes in bread lines in London, infanticide, and even cannibalism throughout Europe.","jurisdictionLevel":0},{"id":1705192,"age":58,"year":"1328","julianDay":2206102,"title":"First War of Scottish Independence","description":"The First War of Scottish Independence began after England invaded Scotland in 1296. The Treaty of Edinburgh was signed in 1328 which declared peace between the two kingdoms and brought the war to an end.","jurisdictionLevel":0}],"lifeSummary":"Mrs Robert Batisford was born about 1270, in England. She had at least 1 daughter with Robert Batisford."},"et":{"about 1270–":"umbes 1270–Surnud","1260–Male":"1260–Surnud","1300–Female":"1300–Surnud","1270–Female":"1270–Surnud","1315":"1315","about 1270":"umbes 1270","1300":"1300","about 1300":"umbes 1300","1260":"1260","1270":"1270","1328":"1328","1317":"1317","1290":"1290","Warbleton, Sussex, England, United Kingdom":"Warbleton, Sussex, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","England":"England"},"fi":{"about 1270–":"noin 1270–Kuollut","1260–Male":"1260–Kuollut","1300–Female":"1300–Kuollut","1270–Female":"1270–Kuollut","1315":"1315","about 1270":"noin 1270","1300":"1300","about 1300":"noin 1300","1260":"1260","1270":"1270","1328":"1328","1317":"1317","1290":"1290","Warbleton, Sussex, England, United Kingdom":"Warbleton, Sussex, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","England":"England"},"fr":{"about 1270–":"environ 12